@node not01 "Editorial"
    ___________                                              _______________
---| EDITORIAL |--------------------------------------------| FATES WARNING |---
    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                                              ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Hello and welcome to the 18th issue of AmiChannel News.

January is usually a very quiet month. There are not a lot of news, and this
month has not been an exception to this rule. Probably the bigger change is the
new layout of the e-magazine. I hope you think it is for better.

Anyway, Amiga has announced its first partner in crime. As I wrote in the
January issue before the announcement was done, this is Tao Group. Everything
seems correct and going well, but it seems that we will see clouds in the sky.

Some days ago, Amiga have released the executive update. It begins like most of
executive update that we have already seen before. Our president remembers the
goals achieved, he confirms the several meetings that he has attended in his
recent trip to Europe and he promise new achievemts, and very soon indeed.
Actually, we have an appointment in two weeks to know a new partner which seems
to be one of the keys for the path Amiga want to follow. As usual, we do not
know clearly what the future is going to be, but Bill has asked Fleecy to write
a document describing some of the ideas which are behind the partnership with
Tao Group.

The title of this editorial is because this is the feeling I have after reading
it. He says that "somebody is going to say something", and he wants us not to
believe him/them, or at least we should wait Amiga to say something. Who knows,
is he warning about a plan to divide the community, perhaps from one of the
companies which attended the meetings not sharing their ideas? Bill want us not
to believe rumours, but he can not avoid us to think about he has just said.
Clearly there are people who have no solution... Anyway there are positive
things in his message, apart from the usual entusiasm.

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located in:

	http://teleline.terra.es/personal/angelsau/index.html

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

	noticias@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
Angel Alvarez Díaz - noticias@saug.org
Editor of the e-magazine AmiChannel News
Responsible of the News Departament of S.A.U.G and Mundo Amiga
Member of C.U.A.E Nº 293 - FOREIGN DIRECTOR
