@node not04 "TNT PROJECT + EVERYTHING NIGHTLONG + PPC"
                    TNT PROJECT + EVERYTHING NIGHTLONG + PPC
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A few years ago, before Myst, Quake, Napalm, T-zer0, Nightlong and Z, we
believed that big games could exist on Amiga... We were right. Now, we claim
that Amiga can compete with other platforms. And we intend to do that with TNT
(The New Tomorrow) Amiga project.

In the ywar 2000, clickBOOM will begin a two-fold TNT project:

  1. To bring you more games, both original and conversions
  2. To support the latest hardware

We believe that at this point in time there is no reason why Amiga should not
have all the great games other platforms have.

If Apple was able to regenerate Mac as a gaming platform, we can do the same
with Amiga !

We feel great about what we have achieved thus far on Amiga. But we also feel we
can do more -- more great games. In the beginning we converted two of the
biggest games in the world, Myst and Quake. Then, we released two great Amiga
original games (Napalm and T-zer0). In 2000 and beyond we want to increase the
number of hits significantly, both conversions and originals. We intend to
revolutionize Amiga game development one more time.

Due to our experience, we could fairly easily obtain licenses for more
conversions. However, our current capacity is not able to handle more
development. To make more games, we'll need more top programmers:

   - To develop original, or convert games from other platforms.
   - 3D programmers with extensive knowledge of Amiga and PC.

If you live and breathe to code in C or ASM, contact us at
http://clickboom.com/contact.shtml

The second part of TNT is our plan to support new hardware. Firstly, we would
like to create games that do not rely on AGA anymore. GFX cards offer a lot of
advantages over AGA, and supporting both is tedious, sometimes even impossible.
Therefore, we are making an appeal to all Amiga owners to switch to gfx cards.

Secondly, we have been favorable towards PPC since its inception, however for
reasons already stated in the past, we have not been able to support it through
our games.

But now, we are ready to take our first steps in developing PPC games.

At this time there are two clickBOOM games which will support PPC: firstly,
there will be a legal Quake PPC, and secondly, there will ve Nightlong PPC.

   - NIGHTLONG HARDWARE SPECS

The greatly anticipated Nightlong is almost ready, and the expected release date
is February 15,2000.

Nightlong is planned to be for GFX cards only. And AGA version is under
consideration, but we can't promise yet whether or not this can be done.

Moreover, Nightlong is the first clickBOOM game to support PPC. The kernel of
choice for it is WarpUp by Haage & partner.

For full hardware details please visit Spects section of the Nightlong site.

Futhermore, since Nightlong is almost finished, preordering is now open.

   - NIGHTLONG PPC

Our first steps in PPC support will be experimental, and Nightlong will be our
first commercial test. We believe in PPC and therefore a PPC module will appear
at the same time as 68K version does, regardless of how many PPC preorders we
get.

However, to justify future PPC development we hope to get 400 preorders for PPC
modules.

If we don't get 400 preorders it will probably mean that it will not be viable
to develop PPC versions of Z and other ganes in the near future.

You will be able to find Nightlong PPC preorder counter at The Portal (Note: at
this moment, there are only 92 preorder for PPC module :().

To prevent piracy, the PPC module in Nightlong will be electronically imprinted
with the personal data of each individual customer.

   - NIGHTLONG PREORDERING

Preordering price for Nightlong is $75 CDN (regular will ve $80 CDN).

PPC module is separate and costs $15 CDN (regular will ve $20 CDN).

If you preorder PPC there is one other added bonus: You can chose to pay only
