@node not14 "DARKAGE SOFTWARE ANNOUNCES TWO NEW TITLES"
                   DARKAGE SOFTWARE ANNOUNCES TWO NEW TITLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Darkage Software have announced two new titles which will be released very soon.

The first one is Powerball, a simple puzzle game where the player must clean
each screen from all the coloured bricks. Doing this is possible by using a ball
that bounces up and down in the screen and that can be controlled by the player
who can move it left or right.

The ball cleans all the same-coloured bricks; to change its colour it has to
touch a brick with two crossed arrows indicating a ball. Other bricks that the
ball can meet are those which are painted with a skull (to avoid, because they
cause the loss of a life), those which can be moved (but not cleaned)
represented by a four-head arrow and those which allow the ball to be teleported
between two points.

Obviously, difficult grows up going on through the levels which compose the game
and examining each screen before starting action could be useful. But you have
to take care of the time limit in each level; running out of time will cause the
loss of a life.

During game, you can collect several bonuses which can increase points or lives,
make you jump to the next level etc. They appear for a few seconds as a brick on
the screen.

The game features:

   - 80 levels in 8 worlds
   - Runs also on an A500!
   - Level editor to add your own levels
   - Only one floppy disk, but it's also hard disk installable!
   - A password system to save your position
   - Loads of fun included in the package! :)

The game will run on any Amiga with 1Mb Ram, and it will available on floppy
disk. The game is scheduled to be released in March 2000. You can download a
demo from http://www.idealia.net/darkage/PowerballDemo.lha

The second title is Amiga Classix 2, the official sequel to one of the most
succesfull Amiga compilation ever! Produced exclusively for Epic Marketing ltd.

It will feature full commercial games by:

   - Darren Ithell (Dithell In Space)
   - Dark Unicorn Productions (Scorched Tanks)
   - Diamond Production (Diamond Caves, Diamond Caves 2, Maniac Ball, Master
     Blaster)
   - Digital Concepts (Island of lost hope, Lords of War, Torch2081)
   - Eclipse Software (Lethal Xcess, Monster Business)
   - Frank Otto (Lost on Parrot Island)
   - Hitek Softworks (Barravento)
   - MegArts (Bomb Mania)
   - Mental Image (Bandit Mania, Technology 2, Winning Post)
   - Scorpius Software (Antz, Blade, Hilt, Hilt 2, Hideous)
   - StarByte (Tiebreak, Hannibal, Space Max, Aunt Artic Adventure, Charon V)
   - Team Hoi (Hoi Aga Remix)
   - and the very famous game Ports of Call!

It will be suitable for both Amiga and PC (you can play all games directly from
the cd, no installation required!). It will run on an Amiga AGA, it will be
CD-Rom only and it will be released in February 2000.

On the other hand, Tales from Heaven have now reached the shops, and Darkage
Software has a big surprise! They have modified the price, reducing it of more
than 10%! Now it costs 79.000 italian lire (40,80Eur). Of course all the people
who preordered from Darkage, they will pay the new price!

The game has 12 levels in 3 worlds, and the production is made with a silver cd
(no gold copies).

More info at http://www.idealia.net/darkage/.
