@node not13 "PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART VII"
                        PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART VII
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

16 January 2000 - The News

It's been a while since the last status report, but that's given me more time to
work on the game, which is starting to get dangerously addictive! This has
frequently slowed down development; several times I've ended up playing the game
for an hour or more rather than actually adding new features! Even so, the
following improvements have been added to the game since last month:

   - Cars now beep at you if you get in their way. Not only that, but some
     drivers are more aggressive than others, which effects all aspects of
     their driving.
   - Police cars now have sirens, complete with flashing lights! (With lens
     flares, of course!)
   - I've started to design more of the map - there's a lot more to explore than
     there was before.
   - More scripting features have been added - garages work properly and you get
     messages sent to you when you do certain things.
   - I fixed a rather major bug that allowed cars to drive up walls. D'oh!
   - Collisions with 'scenery objects' (trees, lampposts, crates, things like
     that) now work brilliantly.
   - The player no longer restarts in the same place every time, which adds a
     bit more variety to the gameplay.
   - Full multi-language support has been added.
   - I added a progress bar to the loading screen.
   - The audio system can now cope with up to 500 sounds at once, which is
     rather more than the previous limit of 100. You might think that this
     would slow the game down, but improvements in efficiency mean that it's
     actually slightly faster than the old system!

Anyway, that's it for this time. Look forward to seeing you next update!

James Daniels
Apex Designs

For more information about Payback, visit
http://www.apex-designs.net/payback.html.
